The paper deals with the design and analysis of routing schemes for wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. However, the use of orthogonal frequency-division multiplexing (OFDM) modulation and the study of the power-bandwidth tradeoff suggest a focus on information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the impact of routing on energy and spectral efficiency, which relates to system optimization (cs.SY) and multimedia systems (cs.MM). Finally, the analysis of channel fading and link reliability suggests a potential connection to cryptography and security (cs.CR).
